title: Cross Country roundup: Cavs take first in Washington
text:
Cross Country roundup: Cavs take first in Washington Gazette Staff 3:22 p.m. EDT October 3, 2015 1 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Blue Lion Cross Country Meet 
The Chillicothe girls finished 1st with 15 points at the Blue Lions Cross Country Meet at Washington Court House. Ella Cuzzolini led the Cavaliers placing 3rd (21:59), Abalena Sullivan finished 6th (23:46), Jasmine Roper followed placing 7th (24:36), Daries Harris finished 11th (26:51) and Mackenzie Elliot placed 12th (27:21). 
The Chillicothe boys also placed 1st with 41 points. Donavan Lowe and Ricky Villereal led the Cavaliers placing 2nd (18:31) and 3rd (18:53). Quentin Boggs followed finishing 5th (19:04). Max Greishiemer placed 12th (20:14) and Jullean Villereal finished 23rd (21:56). 
Piketon Invitational 
Waverly was fifth at the Piketon Invitational (145 points), led by Hunter Hoover (8th, 16:45), Alec Parker (24th, 17:44), Brenden Reed (26th, 17:48), Trevor Penrod (42nd, 18:20) and Brody Sibole (46th, 18:23). 
Zane Trace was eighth (225 points), led by Mark Scott (15th, 17:18), Andrew Graves (33rd, 17:57), Josh Parker (35th, 18:02), Robert Riley (49th, 18:29) and Miah Branson (121st, 20:21). 
Piketon was ninth (241 points), led by Austin Taylor (25th, 17:45), Alex Blanton (37th, 18:08), Jacob Nichols (39th, 18:11), Austin Spencer (71st, 19:08) and Joh Hurst (93rd, 19:43). 
Huntington was twelfth (303 points), led by Gage Hickman (22nd, 17:37), Logan Taylor (62nd, 18:49), Quentin Johnson (68th, 19:06), Nathan Steele (72nd, 19:10) and Dylan Carroll (129th, 20:32). 
Paint Valley was eighteenth (490 points), led by Austin Chapman (83rd, 19:30), P.J. McAllister (113th, 20:10), Noah Davis (126th, 20:29), Patrick Chapman (131st, 20:42) and Adrian Salomone (185th, 22:08). 
Adena was twenty-third (619 points), led by Brandon Wheeler (142nd, 20:53), Cody Cartee (162nd, 21:25), Jordan Howard (182nd, 22:04), Aaron Glandon (204th, 22:49) and Steven Best (225th, 24:47). 
On the girls side of the results, Zane Trace was third (117 points), led by Ivy Beam (9th, 20:06), Alison Chinn (15th, 20:59), McKenzie Ray (31st, 22:00), Hailey Puckett (34th, 22:08) and Taylor Fletchner (35th, 22:12). 
Waverly was fourth (122 points), led by Jamie Welch (6th, 19:52), Leta Heigley (17th, 21:09), Hannah Goodman (23rd, 21:34), Gabby Towler (36th, 22:15) and Kiara Smith (48th, 23:02). 
Adena was thirteenth (313 points), led by Taylor Clarkson (4th, 19:39), Angel Merk (76th, 24:43), Audra Lusk (91st, 25:09), Abby Butler (96th, 25:39) and Hayley Clarkson (125th, 28:06). 
Huntington was fifteenth (362 points), led by Sammie Moore (52nd, 23:20), Josie Tornberg (61st, 23:56), Brittany Moore (99th, 25:48), Ava Carter (116th, 26:52) and Madison Buehrle (119th, 27:10). 
Piketon was sixteenth (409 points), led by Ruthie Wyant (44th, 22:50), Desirae Pollit (104th, 26:02), Bailey Reader (105th, 26:07), Makenzie Wesley (132nd, 29:01) and Ashton Gilbert (137th, 29:14). 
Paint Valley was seventeenth (418 points), led by Emily Davis (86th, 24:56), Colleen Mills (100th, 25:50), Savannah Leeth (106th, 26:09), Olivia Spradlin (115th, 26:46) and Harley Curtis (126th, 28:11). 
Panther Invitational 
Unioto finished second in both boys and girls competition Saturday at the Panther Invitational at Pickerington North. In the girls race the Shermans (118 points) placed second to Shaker Heights (84). Leading Unioto were Haley Wright (eighth, 19:33.4), Alex Evans (15th, 20:06.1), Elena Knipp (22nd, 20:24.3), Tessa Sylvester (34th, 20:47.3) and Abbey Mohan (44th, 21:01.8). 
In the boys race, Unioto (154 points), placed second to Newark (149). Leading Unioto were David Magda (third, 16:13.2), Cole Clever (25th, 17:17.7), Aaron LaPlante (43rd, 17:46.2), Isaiah West (47th, 17:46.7) and Tucker Markko (48th, 17:47.9). 1 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1RnhjEC TOP VIDEOS
